um of its speed, examined the artificial daisies in their little silver vase, the speaking tube hanging on its steel hook, the travelling clock which had its own concept of time, and the ashtray with one gold-tipped cigarette butt in it. A snowy night with aureoled street lights ran past the wide windows.

“I’ll get out here,” he said, recognizing a square and a statue. “It’s just a short walk to my house from here.”

“Oh, I’ll take you there,” replied Dreyer with a little yawn